1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 20=

3
00:01:21,906 --> 00:01:23,666
This car's interior
has had many cleanings.

4
00:01:23,785 --> 00:01:26,466
But the bottom layer of felt
in the truck bed

5
00:01:26,466 --> 00:01:28,386
has been perfectly preserved
all these years.

6
00:01:28,386 --> 00:01:30,585
I detected Ding Youcai's DNA on it.

7
00:01:32,305 --> 00:01:32,986
Also,

8
00:01:33,345 --> 00:01:36,425
the DNA from an unknown female
was found on the phone case.

9
00:01:38,386 --> 00:01:39,986
If it's not the victim's,

10
00:01:40,705 --> 00:01:42,026
it must be the killer's.

11
00:01:42,865 --> 00:01:45,225
It belongs to an unknown female.

12
00:01:49,986 --> 00:01:52,186
So you're resuming your old business?

13
00:01:52,666 --> 00:01:54,626
Or have you never really stopped?

14
00:01:54,945 --> 00:01:56,986
No, I'm just...

15
00:01:59,225 --> 00:02:01,145
Let me put it this way.

16
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:04,585
I do run a travel agency.

17
00:02:05,305 --> 00:02:08,905
I organize group tours abroad
for a few days of fun.

18
00:02:11,145 --> 00:02:14,145
Once they're out,
the local tour operators take over.

19
00:02:14,145 --> 00:02:17,145
I don't know what the local operators
arrange for them to do.

20
00:02:19,266 --> 00:02:23,320
The victims
don't seem to tell the same story.

21
00:02:24,226 --> 00:02:25,745
Don't listen to their nonsense.

22
00:02:25,986 --> 00:02:27,305
What victims?

23
00:02:27,506 --> 00:02:29,145
They are all adults.

24
00:02:29,185 --> 00:02:33,625
The black-and-white contracts
spell everything out clearly.

25
00:02:36,705 --> 00:02:38,106
What about the money you collected?

26
00:02:39,705 --> 00:02:42,066
The bulk goes
to the local tour operators.

27
00:02:42,066 --> 00:02:43,585
I only collect the tour fee.

28
00:02:44,106 --> 00:02:45,016
At most...

29
00:02:46,776 --> 00:02:49,305
At most, there is just a tiny margin.

30
00:02:49,786 --> 00:02:51,066
You have no idea.

31
00:02:51,905 --> 00:02:54,946
Some competitors
are downright unscrupulous.

32
00:02:54,946 --> 00:02:56,465
Utterly immoral.

33
00:02:56,786 --> 00:02:58,666
If you say you're broke,
they'll say it's fine.

34
00:02:58,666 --> 00:03:02,585
They send people to loan sharks
operated by their associates

35
00:03:02,625 --> 00:03:04,025
to borrow at exorbitant rates.

36
00:03:04,465 --> 00:03:08,946
Look. Compared to them,
I run a truly ethical business.

37
00:03:09,826 --> 00:03:14,346
Plus, all my procedures and paperwork
are completely legal.

38
00:03:15,106 --> 00:03:16,905
Why were you in such a rush
to fly southwest?

39
00:03:19,386 --> 00:03:22,905
It's because those people
keep harassing me.

40
00:03:24,506 --> 00:03:26,625
Enough. Let's get serious.

41
00:03:27,506 --> 00:03:29,425
You know about Yu Meigui, right?

42
00:03:31,905 --> 00:03:34,865
You mean Ding Youcai's young wife?

43
00:03:35,905 --> 00:03:37,386
Didn't I say?

44
00:03:37,625 --> 00:03:40,266
I need to check my records.

45
00:03:41,865 --> 00:03:45,145
How come I heard
she's quite close to you?

46
00:03:46,585 --> 00:03:50,025
She goes to your place
for events and gatherings.

47
00:03:55,506 --> 00:03:56,705
I'm warning you.

48
00:03:57,266 --> 00:03:59,106
You've lied to us multiple times.

49
00:04:00,465 --> 00:04:01,976
We now suspect

50
00:04:02,936 --> 00:04:04,824
you're connected to Ding Youcai's death.

51
00:04:05,066 --> 00:04:06,106
No.

52
00:04:06,106 --> 00:04:07,986
It has nothing to do with me. Really.

53
00:04:08,145 --> 00:04:10,145
Did that brat Ding Yu say that?

54
00:04:11,066 --> 00:04:13,625
How could that little brat
slander me like that?

55
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:15,226
I haven't even brought up his mom...

56
00:04:15,226 --> 00:04:18,546
I mean, his stepmother
and their little scandal.

57
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:20,466
Ding Yu and Yu Meigui?

58
00:04:21,226 --> 00:04:24,305
They once borrowed my office
for a gathering.

59
00:04:24,505 --> 00:04:27,065
I happened to need something
and went back.

60
00:04:27,265 --> 00:04:29,146
I saw those two in a car...

61
00:04:31,226 --> 00:04:32,706
It isn't official,

62
00:04:33,466 --> 00:04:36,226
but they're still a son
and his stepmother.

63
00:04:36,226 --> 00:04:38,385
What kind of people are they?

64
00:04:40,546 --> 00:04:42,305
So you told Ding Youcai?

65
00:04:44,106 --> 00:04:46,706
No, I-I didn't.

66
00:04:48,666 --> 00:04:50,026
It's their family business.

67
00:04:50,026 --> 00:04:51,385
I didn't want to meddle.

68
00:04:52,026 --> 00:04:56,305
But I suspect Ding Youcai found out.

69
00:04:56,906 --> 00:04:59,425
Why else would he
keep beating Yu Meigui?

70
00:04:59,786 --> 00:05:01,305
So, according to you,

71
00:05:01,305 --> 00:05:03,865
Ding Youcai frequently abused Yu Meigui?

72
00:05:05,528 --> 00:05:10,865
Well, I shouldn't speak ill of the dead.

73
00:05:11,825 --> 00:05:16,625
But Ding Youcai could be
quite heavy-handed sometimes.

74
00:05:16,952 --> 00:05:18,265
He hit her during her pregnancy.

75
00:05:19,026 --> 00:05:20,305
Yu Meigui was pregnant?

76
00:05:20,706 --> 00:05:21,706
When was that?

77
00:05:23,265 --> 00:05:25,505
About four or five years ago.

78
00:05:25,505 --> 00:05:26,505
What about the child?

79
00:05:26,825 --> 00:05:28,146
I heard she miscarried.

80
00:05:28,305 --> 00:05:29,505
Ding Youcai beat her.

81
00:05:30,666 --> 00:05:32,466
You seem to know quite a lot.

82
00:05:32,546 --> 00:05:33,906
You claim you aren't close to her?

83
00:05:36,425 --> 00:05:38,065
Where is Yu Meigui now?

84
00:05:39,906 --> 00:05:41,146
I don't know.

85
00:05:42,106 --> 00:05:44,146
You'd better think carefully
before answering.

86
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:46,385
I-I really don't know.

87
00:05:46,825 --> 00:05:49,466
I was actually trying
to find her myself.

88
00:05:50,865 --> 00:05:54,346
It happens that foreign wives
run off after marriage,

89
00:05:55,185 --> 00:05:57,346
but so many lately isn't normal.

90
00:05:57,586 --> 00:05:59,666
So I need to find her and ask.

91
00:05:59,786 --> 00:06:02,146
That's why I bought the plane ticket.

92
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:05,986
So you and she were running
the cross-border marriage business?

93
00:06:07,026 --> 00:06:10,385
It's outbound travel. Travel.

94
00:06:16,505 --> 00:06:18,185
The child's mom is named Yu Meigui.

95
00:06:21,346 --> 00:06:24,106
You needed the birth certificate
to register the child.

96
00:06:24,265 --> 00:06:26,786
The birth certificate
lists the mom as Ruan Shihong.

97
00:06:27,265 --> 00:06:29,706
Her passport number
is identical to Yu Meigui's.

98
00:06:32,706 --> 00:06:33,986
I find it strange.

99
00:06:33,986 --> 00:06:37,466
Why did your dad name her Yu Meigui?

100
00:06:37,786 --> 00:06:39,146
Even share your mom's surname.

101
00:06:39,865 --> 00:06:41,226
I named her.

102
00:06:41,945 --> 00:06:43,425
My dad wasn't pleased,

103
00:06:43,906 --> 00:06:44,986
but he didn't object.

104
00:06:46,586 --> 00:06:48,906
So when did you two start?

105
00:06:49,706 --> 00:06:51,546
After she lost her first child.

106
00:06:53,346 --> 00:06:55,786
That child was Ding Youcai's, right?

107
00:07:00,226 --> 00:07:01,706
I called her 'Auntie.'

108
00:07:02,745 --> 00:07:03,546
She refused,

109
00:07:04,026 --> 00:07:06,505
said it aged her,
and told me to call her 'Sis.'

110
00:07:08,226 --> 00:07:11,385
Back then, I did try to see her
as a stepmother.

111
00:07:12,666 --> 00:07:13,656
But she...

112
00:07:14,904 --> 00:07:16,346
She was too young.

113
00:07:16,986 --> 00:07:19,425
And I... I was too young too.

114
00:07:19,466 --> 00:07:21,026
So you acted on impulse, huh?

115
00:07:22,505 --> 00:07:24,945
Originally, we just had
some mutual affection.

116
00:07:25,666 --> 00:07:27,346
Sometimes, if we talked a bit more,

117
00:07:28,185 --> 00:07:29,546
my dad would fly into a rage.

118
00:07:30,425 --> 00:07:31,466
He didn't dare touch me,

119
00:07:31,986 --> 00:07:33,226
so he'd take it out on her.

120
00:07:34,106 --> 00:07:34,945
Try it.

121
00:07:35,065 --> 00:07:35,786
Okay.

122
00:07:41,385 --> 00:07:42,106
Eat more.

123
00:07:43,226 --> 00:07:44,425
See if it's good.

124
00:07:50,346 --> 00:07:51,146
It's good, right?

125
00:08:02,505 --> 00:08:03,546
He hit you again?

126
00:08:09,466 --> 00:08:11,026
Didn't you try to protect her?

127
00:08:11,346 --> 00:08:12,625
Of course I did.

128
00:08:13,185 --> 00:08:15,305
But whenever I explained
or stood up for her,

129
00:08:15,505 --> 00:08:18,625
my dad would be even worse to her
when I wasn't around.

130
00:08:18,666 --> 00:08:20,625
So I took on a lot of part-time jobs,

131
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,146
trying to avoid being alone with her.

132
00:08:23,825 --> 00:08:25,706
My dad was always paranoid.

133
00:08:25,906 --> 00:08:27,906
He never believed the child was his.

134
00:08:27,906 --> 00:08:28,586
So, in the end...

135
00:08:31,986 --> 00:08:35,586
After that, we got together.

136
00:08:36,706 --> 00:08:38,025
She wanted me to take her away.

137
00:08:38,625 --> 00:08:39,385
But I...

138
00:08:40,586 --> 00:08:41,665
Did Ding Youcai find out?

139
00:08:42,986 --> 00:08:45,586
Honestly, I don't know.

140
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:48,306
At least, he never mentioned it
in front of me.

141
00:08:49,986 --> 00:08:53,346
Maybe Meigui
was a bit disappointed in me.

142
00:08:55,306 --> 00:08:58,145
During that time, her relationship
with my dad improved quite a bit.

143
00:08:58,665 --> 00:09:00,186
But not long after,

144
00:09:01,586 --> 00:09:02,986
my dad had that accident.

145
00:09:04,265 --> 00:09:08,545
Did Yu Meigui act strangely
after it happened?

146
00:09:09,665 --> 00:09:10,745
I don't know.

147
00:09:12,265 --> 00:09:14,946
After I found my dad, I called her.

148
00:09:15,665 --> 00:09:16,505
Couldn't get through.

149
00:09:18,986 --> 00:09:20,785
So you didn't call the police
right away?

150
00:09:21,545 --> 00:09:23,905
You thought Yu Meigui
was the killer, didn't you?

151
00:09:26,145 --> 00:09:27,265
Listen to me!

152
00:09:29,905 --> 00:09:32,426
We've gathered a lot of evidence.

153
00:09:34,186 --> 00:09:36,106
If you keep being evasive like this,

154
00:09:37,186 --> 00:09:39,706
it will only add
to your culpability, understand?

155
00:09:40,426 --> 00:09:42,066
For that meal my dad didn't finish,

156
00:09:43,066 --> 00:09:45,385
the lunchbox was brought from home.

157
00:09:46,625 --> 00:09:48,426
That dish tasted just like her hometown.

158
00:09:48,426 --> 00:09:49,905
No one else could make it.

159
00:09:51,706 --> 00:09:53,466
After I cleaned that up

160
00:09:53,466 --> 00:09:56,426
and got home,
I found her luggage was gone.

161
00:09:57,586 --> 00:09:58,986
Her phone was turned off too.

162
00:10:02,066 --> 00:10:04,186
I didn't know how to face her.

163
00:10:05,226 --> 00:10:09,145
I thought, if she's gone, so be it.

164
00:10:10,946 --> 00:10:12,306
I never expected that one day,

165
00:10:14,625 --> 00:10:15,745
she would come back.

166
00:10:25,466 --> 00:10:26,145
Ding Yu,

167
00:10:26,905 --> 00:10:27,986
someone's here for you.

168
00:10:28,426 --> 00:10:29,186
For me?

169
00:10:29,186 --> 00:10:29,745
Yeah.

170
00:10:44,025 --> 00:10:44,905
Meigui?

171
00:10:53,625 --> 00:10:55,466
A few days
after giving birth to that child,

172
00:10:55,466 --> 00:10:56,265
she left again.

173
00:10:56,946 --> 00:10:57,986
I didn't look for her.

174
00:10:58,745 --> 00:11:00,986
I figured she probably
wouldn't come back.

175
00:11:03,946 --> 00:11:05,745
Didn't you ask her about your dad?

176
00:11:09,385 --> 00:11:11,186
Haven't you been in touch these years?

177
00:11:11,426 --> 00:11:12,066
No.

178
00:11:18,106 --> 00:11:21,785
Raising a child alone
must be really tough.

179
00:11:23,066 --> 00:11:25,346
Haven't you thought
about finding someone else?

180
00:11:26,665 --> 00:11:28,426
F-Find someone else?

181
00:11:30,265 --> 00:11:31,186
Here's the thing.

182
00:11:33,545 --> 00:11:35,306
I was young back then

183
00:11:37,826 --> 00:11:39,346
and wasn't able to protect my mom.

184
00:11:41,706 --> 00:11:43,946
When I grew up,
I couldn't protect her either.

185
00:11:46,505 --> 00:11:47,545
And my dad...

186
00:11:49,265 --> 00:11:50,785
I failed him too.

187
00:11:53,025 --> 00:11:56,186
I'm not someone reliable.

188
00:11:57,385 --> 00:11:59,586
So I shouldn't drag anyone else down.

189
00:12:05,745 --> 00:12:07,346
Come on.

190
00:12:08,826 --> 00:12:10,826
What are you two talking about?

191
00:12:11,785 --> 00:12:12,306
You guys eat.

192
00:12:12,306 --> 00:12:14,066
Don't pry into women's talk.

193
00:12:14,745 --> 00:12:16,145
I'll go clean the kitchen. Eat up.

194
00:12:16,545 --> 00:12:17,865
Come on. Let's eat.

195
00:12:18,265 --> 00:12:21,545
What's with Jing? She seems so happy.

196
00:12:21,785 --> 00:12:23,265
Just happy for no reason.

197
00:12:23,706 --> 00:12:24,865
What else could it be?

198
00:12:30,905 --> 00:12:31,946
Let me ask you something.

199
00:12:33,106 --> 00:12:36,346
Have you noticed Little Qian
being all secretive lately?

200
00:12:36,986 --> 00:12:38,106
On a mission, probably.

201
00:12:39,265 --> 00:12:40,066
What mission?

202
00:12:41,586 --> 00:12:42,466
You want to know?

203
00:12:46,466 --> 00:12:47,265
Eat your noodles.

204
00:12:50,586 --> 00:12:51,306
What?

205
00:12:51,946 --> 00:12:52,706
Eat your noodles.

206
00:12:56,226 --> 00:12:57,665
Everyone's being mysterious, huh?

207
00:12:57,865 --> 00:12:58,466
Okay.

208
00:13:20,905 --> 00:13:21,946
Here's what we think.

209
00:13:22,106 --> 00:13:25,625
Bao Hei is sending you to Huashan
for two reasons.

210
00:13:26,025 --> 00:13:28,145
First, to test Huo and his gang

211
00:13:28,226 --> 00:13:33,226
and see if they can run safe shipments
to Wannan and Yunxi.

212
00:13:34,226 --> 00:13:35,466
Second, to test you.

213
00:13:35,466 --> 00:13:38,025
Bao Hei is interested
in your fake identity.

214
00:13:38,625 --> 00:13:41,466
Someone's been investigating
your background lately.

215
00:13:41,865 --> 00:13:45,426
We're gradually
identifying everyone involved.

216
00:13:47,145 --> 00:13:48,905
This mission is extremely challenging.

217
00:13:49,426 --> 00:13:51,865
You'll face
many unimaginable difficulties.

218
00:13:53,785 --> 00:13:55,745
You must be extremely cautious.

219
00:13:56,265 --> 00:13:58,106
Abort the mission if necessary.

220
00:14:00,106 --> 00:14:00,826
Ye,

221
00:14:01,106 --> 00:14:02,106
safety first.

222
00:14:04,186 --> 00:14:04,986
Got it.

223
00:14:23,265 --> 00:14:24,385
Don't get your car wet.

224
00:14:25,226 --> 00:14:25,986
It's fine.

225
00:14:27,066 --> 00:14:27,946
Where are they?

226
00:14:28,145 --> 00:14:29,545
Didn't I tell you already?

227
00:14:29,625 --> 00:14:30,586
It's just us today.

228
00:14:46,385 --> 00:14:47,186
Which way?

229
00:14:48,905 --> 00:14:49,905
Follow the GPS.

230
00:14:50,426 --> 00:14:51,466
Head toward Huashan first.

231
00:14:51,706 --> 00:14:52,785
I'll guide you when nearer.

232
00:15:19,385 --> 00:15:22,905
Bao Hei insisted those two
go to Huashan alone.

233
00:15:23,265 --> 00:15:24,145
He's up to no good.

234
00:15:29,505 --> 00:15:30,265
Madman,

235
00:15:30,826 --> 00:15:33,586
after eating, come with me
to Huashan for a look.

236
00:15:34,865 --> 00:15:37,385
That'd openly show Bao Hei
we don't trust him.

237
00:15:38,385 --> 00:15:39,905
We won't be able to proceed afterward.

238
00:15:41,145 --> 00:15:42,106
In Qing's opinion,

239
00:15:42,785 --> 00:15:45,145
Bao Hei mainly wants
to test Ye Qian's capabilities.

240
00:15:46,226 --> 00:15:47,905
Since he's interested in Ye Qian,

241
00:15:48,905 --> 00:15:51,865
they probably won't face
any real danger, right?

242
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:53,665
Nothing serious.

243
00:15:54,346 --> 00:15:54,986
Perfect.

244
00:15:55,346 --> 00:15:56,586
While the tail's gone,

245
00:15:56,946 --> 00:15:58,106
let's handle our business.

246
00:16:07,346 --> 00:16:07,946
Ziwu.

247
00:16:09,346 --> 00:16:10,306
Perfect timing.

248
00:16:10,586 --> 00:16:12,226
The DNA test results are in.

249
00:16:12,426 --> 00:16:16,025
It's a maternal match between
the unknown female and Ding Yu's child.

250
00:16:16,186 --> 00:16:19,106
Meaning the texts and calls that night

251
00:16:19,106 --> 00:16:20,905
were both handled by Yu Meigui?

252
00:16:21,226 --> 00:16:23,186
Her blood
was on the phone case and buttons.

253
00:16:23,186 --> 00:16:24,306
She's now the prime suspect.

254
00:16:24,306 --> 00:16:25,306
- Captain Leng.
- But...

255
00:16:26,426 --> 00:16:28,785
We had Fang Qihang
contact Yu Meigui as you instructed.

256
00:16:28,785 --> 00:16:30,426
Yu Meigui is now on a flight to Yunxi.

257
00:16:30,426 --> 00:16:31,466
She lands in two hours.

258
00:16:32,385 --> 00:16:33,265
What did you just say?

259
00:16:33,265 --> 00:16:34,025
See for yourself.

260
00:16:34,145 --> 00:16:34,706
Okay.

261
00:16:34,865 --> 00:16:35,466
Let's go.

262
00:16:35,466 --> 00:16:36,186
We're off, Zhang.

263
00:16:58,665 --> 00:16:59,905
Captain Leng, heads up.

264
00:17:00,265 --> 00:17:02,025
Yu Meigui is exiting through Gate 2 now.

265
00:17:03,346 --> 00:17:04,226
Copy that.

266
00:17:34,345 --> 00:17:35,025
Follow her.

267
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:16,584
♪After all, we've grown up
a bit these past few years♪

268
00:18:18,107 --> 00:18:23,859
♪Looking back at old times,
there's a touch of sweetness♪

269
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:31,665
♪If time could flow backwards,
could the past be revisited?♪

270
00:18:31,992 --> 00:18:36,491
♪Do your best and don't let go♪

271
00:18:39,217 --> 00:18:44,827
♪You said those moments
from the past burned us both♪

272
00:18:46,264 --> 00:18:51,834
♪Though the story found no end,
and the promise broke♪

273
00:18:53,205 --> 00:18:59,575
♪That so-called happiness
became pain without a place to land♪

274
00:18:59,575 --> 00:19:05,627
♪All the rights and wrongs
will fade away♪

275
00:19:07,448 --> 00:19:14,136
♪I really want to know
where you landed later♪

276
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:21,112
♪So many words I've wanted to say,
yet I find myself speechless♪

277
00:19:21,528 --> 00:19:26,872
♪This world is too big,
but longing doesn't fear distance♪

278
00:19:26,872 --> 00:19:33,856
♪Make a wish upon a shooting star,
may it come true♪

279
00:19:33,856 --> 00:19:40,942
♪Perhaps I still can't let go
in my heart♪

280
00:19:40,942 --> 00:19:46,025
♪Time never lingers for love's sake♪

281
00:19:46,025 --> 00:19:47,345
You came out alone with me.

282
00:19:48,505 --> 00:19:50,386
Your partner doesn't mind?

283
00:19:51,866 --> 00:19:52,785
Do you care?

284
00:19:56,626 --> 00:19:57,426
What about you?

285
00:19:58,305 --> 00:19:59,265
Me?

286
00:20:02,146 --> 00:20:03,265
I don't care about anyone.

287
00:20:05,016 --> 00:20:09,208
♪Remember this♪

288
00:20:36,825 --> 00:20:37,866
Fill it with 92, please.

289
00:20:37,866 --> 00:20:38,426
Sure.

290
00:21:06,186 --> 00:21:06,906
Let's go.

291
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:21,373
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

292
00:21:25,167 --> 00:21:30,488
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

293
00:21:32,561 --> 00:21:37,415
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

294
00:21:38,221 --> 00:21:41,368
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

295
00:21:41,368 --> 00:21:44,472
♪To shield us from the storm♪

296
00:21:47,128 --> 00:21:52,262
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

297
00:21:54,232 --> 00:21:59,864
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

298
00:22:01,624 --> 00:22:05,208
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

299
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:13,800
♪Converging into your form♪

300
00:22:14,232 --> 00:22:16,910
♪Looking up♪

301
00:22:16,910 --> 00:22:20,449
♪Such dazzling glory♪

302
00:22:21,432 --> 00:22:23,992
♪Like hope♪

303
00:22:23,992 --> 00:22:27,925
♪Reaching out its arms♪

304
00:22:28,792 --> 00:22:31,444
♪Cloaked in light♪

305
00:22:31,444 --> 00:22:35,928
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

306
00:22:35,928 --> 00:22:38,744
♪Traversing♪

307
00:22:38,744 --> 00:22:45,255
♪The battlefield of fate♪

308
00:22:52,386 --> 00:22:53,105
Captain Leng,

309
00:22:53,906 --> 00:22:55,545
I asked the property management.

310
00:22:55,785 --> 00:22:57,025
They recognized Yu Meigui

311
00:22:57,025 --> 00:22:59,545
as the tenant of Unit 202, Building 1.

312
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:01,146
She's rented here for years.

313
00:23:01,386 --> 00:23:02,545
Also, they mentioned

314
00:23:02,545 --> 00:23:04,265
that apartment
likely houses many people.

315
00:23:04,265 --> 00:23:06,345
New faces are constantly
coming and going.

316
00:23:06,345 --> 00:23:07,785
All relatively young women.

317
00:23:08,466 --> 00:23:12,105
Notify the precinct
to send female officers.

318
00:23:12,305 --> 00:23:13,825
Foreigners might be involved.

319
00:23:13,825 --> 00:23:14,226
Okay.

320
00:23:14,226 --> 00:23:15,305
Give them a heads-up.

321
00:23:15,466 --> 00:23:16,386
- Okay.
- Go now.

322
00:23:23,305 --> 00:23:24,706
Didn't I already tell you?

323
00:23:25,706 --> 00:23:26,505
Where are you from?

324
00:23:30,265 --> 00:23:31,386
When did you arrive?

325
00:23:32,585 --> 00:23:33,545
I don't remember.

326
00:23:44,146 --> 00:23:44,946
Yu Meigui,

327
00:23:44,946 --> 00:23:48,585
a marriage scam for financial gain
is a crime in our country,

328
00:23:48,585 --> 00:23:49,345
you know?

329
00:23:51,505 --> 00:23:53,305
How can you call that a scam?

330
00:23:54,265 --> 00:23:56,946
We followed the legal requirements

331
00:23:57,345 --> 00:24:00,505
and got legally married
as soon as we entered the country.

332
00:24:02,025 --> 00:24:04,065
The law guarantees freedom of marriage

333
00:24:04,626 --> 00:24:06,305
and protects women's rights.

334
00:24:07,706 --> 00:24:12,426
Besides, matters of the heart
are always mutual.

335
00:24:13,146 --> 00:24:15,105
The girls want to leave
because they're unwilling.

336
00:24:17,706 --> 00:24:19,505
Your government should be protecting us.

337
00:24:21,505 --> 00:24:24,545
Shouldn't divorce be handled
at the marriage registration office?

338
00:24:26,105 --> 00:24:27,906
If parting ways could be that easy,

339
00:24:28,426 --> 00:24:29,906
why go to all this trouble?

340
00:24:30,785 --> 00:24:33,386
After all, I was the one
who introduced them.

341
00:24:34,105 --> 00:24:35,585
I have to take some responsibility.

342
00:24:35,946 --> 00:24:39,025
Whenever they encounter those
who like to get violent,

343
00:24:39,265 --> 00:24:40,825
and the marriage becomes unbearable,

344
00:24:42,906 --> 00:24:44,545
I need to give them an escape route

345
00:24:45,105 --> 00:24:45,906
and a safety net.

346
00:24:47,386 --> 00:24:50,545
That must be a lesson learned
from your own experience, right?

347
00:24:55,866 --> 00:24:57,946
We've found Ding Youcai.

348
00:25:03,626 --> 00:25:04,745
Do you remember him?

349
00:25:07,025 --> 00:25:08,906
We've also found that taxi.

350
00:25:10,025 --> 00:25:12,745
Ding Yu cleaned that car back then.

351
00:25:14,105 --> 00:25:16,946
But some evidence can't be washed away.

352
00:25:20,745 --> 00:25:24,146
Don't you want to know
what Ding Yu said?

353
00:25:31,785 --> 00:25:33,226
No matter what Ding Yu said,

354
00:25:34,505 --> 00:25:35,706
I didn't kill Ding Youcai.

355
00:25:44,426 --> 00:25:49,146
That day, we girls from the same place
were having a gathering.

356
00:25:50,426 --> 00:25:52,345
Midway through,
I got a call from Ding Youcai.

357
00:25:52,345 --> 00:25:53,305
He told me to see him.

358
00:25:57,545 --> 00:26:00,946
He sounded drunk on the phone.

359
00:26:01,466 --> 00:26:02,906
He seemed agitated.

360
00:26:05,226 --> 00:26:06,305
I didn't want to go.

361
00:26:07,305 --> 00:26:10,585
But I knew if I pissed him off,

362
00:26:11,505 --> 00:26:13,785
I'd be the one getting hurt
when he lashed out.

363
00:26:14,825 --> 00:26:15,906
So I went.

364
00:26:18,265 --> 00:26:19,785
When I got there...

365
00:27:08,426 --> 00:27:10,065
I never deleted the photo.

366
00:27:11,105 --> 00:27:13,745
I kept it, thinking
it might be useful someday.

367
00:27:15,545 --> 00:27:16,706
Why not call the police?

368
00:27:17,666 --> 00:27:19,305
I was afraid the police
would suspect me.

369
00:27:20,505 --> 00:27:21,304
Mainly because

370
00:27:22,328 --> 00:27:24,792
my visa wasn't
exactly compliant back then.

371
00:27:26,296 --> 00:27:27,706
I didn't want to go.

372
00:27:29,105 --> 00:27:30,505
So you went to Ding Yu?

373
00:27:33,025 --> 00:27:34,386
Ding Yu suspected me too.

374
00:27:36,205 --> 00:27:37,505
But he wouldn't call the police.

375
00:27:38,305 --> 00:27:39,146
I knew that.

376
00:27:41,146 --> 00:27:43,825
I used Ding Youcai's phone to call him.

377
00:27:59,608 --> 00:28:01,304
(Ding Yu)

378
00:28:19,032 --> 00:28:21,464
(Cover my shift in South City)

379
00:28:54,105 --> 00:28:57,626
Later, I went to stay
with the other girls here.

380
00:29:01,906 --> 00:29:03,105
About the photo,

381
00:29:03,928 --> 00:29:05,226
had you seen this person before?

382
00:29:08,466 --> 00:29:11,745
I-It was too dark that night,

383
00:29:12,785 --> 00:29:14,386
and I was too nervous.

384
00:29:15,186 --> 00:29:16,146
I couldn't see clearly.

385
00:29:16,706 --> 00:29:19,626
One photo alone
doesn't clear you of suspicion.

386
00:29:19,825 --> 00:29:21,745
Plus, you had a motive
to kill Ding Youcai.

387
00:29:22,545 --> 00:29:23,666
It really wasn't me.

388
00:29:30,946 --> 00:29:32,186
Fang Qihang.

389
00:29:33,186 --> 00:29:33,906
Why?

390
00:29:34,025 --> 00:29:35,386
Fang Qihang. It should be him.

391
00:29:36,105 --> 00:29:38,345
D-Ding Youcai paid 100,000 to buy me.

392
00:29:38,466 --> 00:29:40,745
But my bride price,

393
00:29:40,745 --> 00:29:43,706
the fees, and the tolls
shouldn't have totaled more than 50,000.

394
00:29:43,946 --> 00:29:46,745
Fang Qihang pocketed the other 50,000.

395
00:29:48,545 --> 00:29:51,025
Fang Qihang, you liar!

396
00:29:51,345 --> 00:29:53,105
That woman's only worth 50,000.

397
00:29:53,226 --> 00:29:54,626
And you charged me 100,000?

398
00:29:55,105 --> 00:29:56,585
Don't let me find you.

399
00:29:56,785 --> 00:29:59,065
If I find you, I'll kill you!

400
00:30:03,226 --> 00:30:03,906
Let's go.

401
00:30:04,585 --> 00:30:05,688
Let's settle this with him.

402
00:30:06,008 --> 00:30:06,706
Move!

403
00:30:08,825 --> 00:30:10,305
Have you seen that knife?

404
00:30:13,745 --> 00:30:16,345
Ding Youcai used that thing
to scare me plenty.

405
00:30:17,825 --> 00:30:19,386
Sometimes when he was in a bad mood,

406
00:30:20,386 --> 00:30:21,825
he'd threaten me with it.

407
00:30:22,866 --> 00:30:24,600
He wouldn't dare act up
if Ding Yu's there.

408
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:29,825
Did you touch Ding Youcai's body?

409
00:30:33,186 --> 00:30:34,706
Ding Youcai was afraid I'd run away.

410
00:30:34,866 --> 00:30:38,986
He always kept my passport
and residence permit on him.

411
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:43,745
That night when I went to get them,

412
00:30:43,745 --> 00:30:44,706
I was so scared.

413
00:30:45,025 --> 00:30:47,626
I even cut my hand on his zipper pull.

414
00:30:57,345 --> 00:30:58,906
The DNA test results are in.

415
00:30:59,186 --> 00:31:02,785
It's a maternal match between
the unknown female and Ding Yu's child.

416
00:31:02,946 --> 00:31:05,825
Meaning the texts and calls that night

417
00:31:05,825 --> 00:31:07,666
were both handled by Yu Meigui?

418
00:31:07,986 --> 00:31:09,866
Her blood
was on the phone case and buttons.

419
00:31:09,866 --> 00:31:10,986
She's now the prime suspect.

420
00:31:21,785 --> 00:31:22,426
Hungry?

421
00:31:22,986 --> 00:31:24,226
Want to eat something?

422
00:31:24,866 --> 00:31:26,505
But there are only instant noodles here.

423
00:31:26,986 --> 00:31:29,105
Or should we drive a bit further

424
00:31:29,146 --> 00:31:30,466
and eat once we reach the city?

425
00:31:31,666 --> 00:31:32,666
Instant noodles are fine.

426
00:31:33,226 --> 00:31:33,866
Okay.

427
00:31:34,946 --> 00:31:35,785
Add a sausage.

428
00:31:36,585 --> 00:31:37,265
Okay.

429
00:31:40,986 --> 00:31:41,505
Ma'am,

430
00:31:41,825 --> 00:31:42,745
one sausage

431
00:31:42,906 --> 00:31:44,146
(Through the pain, no tears fall)
and two instant noodles.

432
00:31:44,280 --> 00:31:45,190
(You promised to grow old with me)
How much?

433
00:31:45,505 --> 00:31:46,386
Eighteen yuan.

434
00:31:50,904 --> 00:31:52,856
(One more moment, just hold me)

435
00:32:02,105 --> 00:32:02,785
Sir,

436
00:32:02,986 --> 00:32:04,105
I want to sing a song.

437
00:32:04,626 --> 00:32:05,585
Sure. What song?

438
00:32:10,426 --> 00:32:11,426
What do you like?

439
00:32:13,816 --> 00:32:19,400
♪After all, we've grown up
a bit these past few years♪

440
00:32:20,923 --> 00:32:26,675
♪Looking back at old times,
there's a touch of sweetness♪

441
00:32:27,896 --> 00:32:34,481
♪If time could flow backwards,
could the past be revisited?♪

442
00:32:34,808 --> 00:32:39,307
♪Do your best and don't let go♪

443
00:32:42,033 --> 00:32:47,643
♪You said those moments
from the past burned us both♪

444
00:32:52,505 --> 00:32:53,265
Chen Yumo,

445
00:32:54,666 --> 00:32:57,666
I want to go to the same college as you.

446
00:32:59,146 --> 00:33:00,265
I want it too.

447
00:33:03,785 --> 00:33:05,345
What did you say? I didn't hear it.

448
00:33:05,345 --> 00:33:06,065
Say it again.

449
00:33:06,825 --> 00:33:07,785
Never mind.

450
00:33:08,986 --> 00:33:09,825
I heard it.

451
00:33:09,986 --> 00:33:11,386
You said you want it too, right?

452
00:33:11,585 --> 00:33:12,345
Nonsense.

453
00:33:12,706 --> 00:33:13,345
You said it.

454
00:33:13,666 --> 00:33:14,186
I heard it.

455
00:33:14,186 --> 00:33:14,706
I didn't.

456
00:33:14,706 --> 00:33:15,466
I heard it.

457
00:33:15,745 --> 00:33:16,666
I didn't say it.

458
00:33:17,144 --> 00:33:18,226
You said you like me too.

459
00:33:18,906 --> 00:33:19,466
I didn't.

460
00:33:19,466 --> 00:33:20,025
You said.

461
00:33:20,426 --> 00:33:21,345
You misheard me.

462
00:33:21,666 --> 00:33:22,466
I didn't say it.

463
00:33:31,226 --> 00:33:32,505
Where were you then?

464
00:33:32,866 --> 00:33:33,906
I couldn't find you.

465
00:33:37,666 --> 00:33:38,986
I wanted to find you.

466
00:33:39,825 --> 00:33:41,186
But my dad wouldn't let me go out.

467
00:33:42,466 --> 00:33:43,345
Not sincere enough.

468
00:33:43,946 --> 00:33:45,906
Couldn't you have found a way to go out?

469
00:33:46,745 --> 00:33:48,666
Besides, didn't you have your phone?

470
00:33:48,986 --> 00:33:50,305
Your dad took it too?

471
00:33:53,226 --> 00:33:54,025
Yeah.

472
00:33:55,706 --> 00:33:57,505
But I still managed to sneak out.

473
00:33:58,305 --> 00:33:59,505
On the day you moved.

474
00:34:34,585 --> 00:34:36,346
Yumo? Yumo.

475
00:34:37,145 --> 00:34:38,105
Yumo!

476
00:34:39,386 --> 00:34:40,266
Yumo!

477
00:34:42,386 --> 00:34:43,225
Yumo!

478
00:34:47,665 --> 00:34:48,386
Yumo!

479
00:34:51,306 --> 00:34:51,986
Yumo!

480
00:35:17,346 --> 00:35:19,306
Did you become a cop out of guilt?

481
00:35:30,826 --> 00:35:31,866
You felt

482
00:35:33,065 --> 00:35:34,025
guilty toward me.

483
00:35:35,266 --> 00:35:36,225
You wanted to help me

484
00:35:36,866 --> 00:35:37,866
and protect me.

485
00:35:40,386 --> 00:35:41,065
Is that right?

486
00:36:00,786 --> 00:36:01,505
Forget it.

487
00:36:03,346 --> 00:36:04,786
It's been so long.

488
00:36:06,105 --> 00:36:07,185
I've let it go.

489
00:36:09,386 --> 00:36:10,266
You should too.

490
00:36:15,025 --> 00:36:16,065
As for now,

491
00:36:17,025 --> 00:36:20,025
we'll each get what we need.

492
00:36:23,060 --> 00:36:23,960
Good working with you.

493
00:36:37,305 --> 00:36:38,185
Good working with you.

494
00:36:40,625 --> 00:36:42,225
I've clarified the photo.

495
00:36:42,225 --> 00:36:43,705
Yu Meigui has a point.

496
00:36:43,866 --> 00:36:45,466
Judging by the height and build,

497
00:36:45,665 --> 00:36:47,505
this person does look a lot
like Fang Qihang,

498
00:36:47,705 --> 00:36:49,585
especially with him
rolling up his sleeves.

499
00:36:49,705 --> 00:36:51,786
Even the height matches Fang Qihang's.

500
00:36:51,946 --> 00:36:52,545
Captain Leng,

501
00:36:53,386 --> 00:36:54,946
we verified with the telecom company.

502
00:36:54,946 --> 00:36:57,986
Yu Meigui did receive Ding Youcai's call
during the crime window.

503
00:36:58,065 --> 00:37:01,585
Her claim about attending
a hometown gathering was also confirmed.

504
00:37:01,786 --> 00:37:05,505
The incident where Fang Qihang scammed
Ding Youcai out of 50,000 is also true.

505
00:37:05,786 --> 00:37:07,625
Fang Qihang
had a business partner back then.

506
00:37:07,786 --> 00:37:08,826
According to him,

507
00:37:08,826 --> 00:37:10,746
Fang Qihang started
by scamming acquaintances.

508
00:37:10,746 --> 00:37:12,786
His earliest clients
were all people he knew.

509
00:37:12,786 --> 00:37:14,625
Ding Youcai wasn't the only one
he scammed.

510
00:37:14,625 --> 00:37:18,466
Plus, Ding Youcai repeatedly
visited their office to make threats

511
00:37:18,466 --> 00:37:19,786
to sue Fang Qihang for fraud.

512
00:37:20,105 --> 00:37:23,466
Yu Meigui's blood was found
on the victim's phone case and buttons.

513
00:37:23,705 --> 00:37:26,466
I thought she cut herself
while stabbing with the push dagger.

514
00:37:27,225 --> 00:37:30,025
But she said it happened while unzipping
his jacket to find her ID.

515
00:37:30,386 --> 00:37:32,705
She didn't deliberately
hide this crucial detail.

516
00:37:33,746 --> 00:37:37,065
Plus, piercing a skull barehanded
requires immense strength.

517
00:37:38,466 --> 00:37:41,145
Given her physical condition,
Yu Meigui couldn't have done it.

518
00:37:43,386 --> 00:37:44,705
So if that's the case.

519
00:37:44,705 --> 00:37:48,946
Ding Yu, Yu Meigui, and Fang Qihang
are all suspects.

520
00:37:48,946 --> 00:37:52,545
But our current evidence
can't confirm or rule out anyone.

521
00:37:54,946 --> 00:37:56,346
I have an idea.

522
00:38:01,065 --> 00:38:01,906
The rain stopped.

523
00:38:11,266 --> 00:38:12,065
A rainbow.

524
00:39:00,145 --> 00:39:00,946
Number one.

525
00:39:02,585 --> 00:39:03,386
Push dagger.

526
00:39:04,946 --> 00:39:06,386
Cooperate with us for an experiment.

527
00:39:07,266 --> 00:39:08,946
Right back of the head. Stab hard.

528
00:39:55,866 --> 00:39:56,786
Is this okay?

529
00:39:57,426 --> 00:39:58,225
That's enough.

530
00:40:08,185 --> 00:40:08,986
Number two.

531
00:40:13,105 --> 00:40:14,466
Please cooperate with us.

532
00:40:14,545 --> 00:40:16,105
Right back of the head. Stab hard.

533
00:40:50,065 --> 00:40:50,866
Number three.

534
00:40:55,545 --> 00:40:57,145
Please cooperate with us.

535
00:40:57,145 --> 00:40:57,866
Officer,

536
00:40:58,025 --> 00:40:59,266
is this really necessary?

537
00:41:00,225 --> 00:41:01,346
It really wasn't me.

538
00:41:01,346 --> 00:41:03,266
T-This is so unlucky.

539
00:41:04,625 --> 00:41:06,545
Right back of the head. Stab hard.

540
00:41:52,585 --> 00:41:53,866
Wait, look.

541
00:41:53,866 --> 00:41:56,185
I really don't know
how to use this thing.

542
00:41:57,185 --> 00:41:58,545
The clear need no clearing.

543
00:41:58,866 --> 00:41:59,906
You look a bit guilty.

544
00:42:06,306 --> 00:42:07,105
Tape measure.

545
00:42:25,448 --> 00:42:28,941
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

546
00:42:32,735 --> 00:42:38,056
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

547
00:42:40,129 --> 00:42:44,983
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

548
00:42:45,789 --> 00:42:48,936
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

549
00:42:48,936 --> 00:42:52,040
♪To shield us from the storm♪

550
00:42:54,696 --> 00:42:59,830
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

551
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:07,432
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

552
00:43:09,192 --> 00:43:12,776
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

553
00:43:13,928 --> 00:43:21,368
♪Converging into your form♪

554
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:24,478
♪Looking up♪

555
00:43:24,478 --> 00:43:28,017
♪Such dazzling glory♪

556
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:31,560
♪Like hope♪

557
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:35,493
♪Reaching out its arms♪

558
00:43:36,360 --> 00:43:39,012
♪Cloaked in light♪

559
00:43:39,012 --> 00:43:43,496
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

560
00:43:43,496 --> 00:43:46,312
♪Traversing♪

561
00:43:46,312 --> 00:43:52,823
♪The battlefield of fate♪
